                                                   World meet in Hyderabad
            A STAFF REPORTER                      
	Calcutta: The biggest global badminton tournament, the World Badminton Championships (WBC), will be held in Hyderabad from August 10-16. The event, in which over 50 countries will be participating, will be staged at the Gachibowli stadium.         
	The event will also serve as a preparation before the country hosts the 2010 Commonwealth Games. India will also be hosting the World Cup of mens field hockey.         
	The Badminton Association of India president VK Verma said India was aware of the importance of such events and would do everything to make them a roaring success.         
	To host events of these statures we need to have our infrastructure and technology in place in accordance to the norms of international standards. Former player Prakash Padukone also welcomed the development and said that it could not get bigger for Indian badminton.                                                                                                                       
